sourceMeaningMnemonic: A <radical>mole</radical> in <radical>winter</radical> will <kanji>do</kanji> whatever you ask, if you know how to ask it.
meaningInfo: They do most of their own chores during the rest of the year, so winter is when you should ask them to do things for you.
readingMnemonic: To get the mole to <kanji>do</kanji> what you want, just give it a nice big hunk of <reading>chee</reading>se (<ja>ち</ja>).
readingInfo: Moles will do anything for cheese, but honestly, wouldn't we all?
